---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="WastelandWares — a solo developer studio building with AI-native development.">
  <section class="about-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-header animate-fade-in">
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">
          A solo developer studio where precision engineering meets creative freedom.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-content">
        <div class="about-section animate-fade-in animate-delay-1">
          <h2>Building in the Wasteland</h2>
          <p>
            The tech landscape is a wasteland of abandoned projects, half-finished frameworks,
            and tools that promise everything but deliver nothing. WastelandWares builds things
            that survive.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every product in the portfolio solves a real problem. Not a hypothetical problem
            from a pitch deck — a problem encountered in the daily work of building software.
            claude-gate exists because AI agents needed guardrails. The orchestrator exists
            because running multiple agents needed coordination. The dungeon crawler exists
            because sometimes you need to build something just for the craft of it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section animate-fade-in animate-delay-2">
          <h2>AI-Native Development</h2>
          <p>
            WastelandWares is built with AI agents, not just by a human who uses AI.
            The orchestrator coordinates teams of Claude agents. Each agent has a persona,
            a worktree, and a mission. The human provides direction and review.
            The agents build.
          </p>
          <p>
            This isn't a gimmick — it's a development methodology. The dungeon-crawler
            was built entirely by AI agents from the first line of code. The orchestrator
            that coordinates those agents was itself largely built by agents. It's
            infrastructure all the way down.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section animate-fade-in animate-delay-3">
          <h2>The Portfolio</h2>
          <p>
            The range is intentional. Auth tools teach you about security boundaries.
            Games teach you about rendering and state management. Meeting transcription
            teaches you about real-time audio processing. A programming language teaches
            you about compilers and type systems. Each project makes the others better.
          </p>
          <div class="stack-list">
            <div class="stack-item">
              <span class="stack-label">Languages</span>
              <span class="stack-value">Rust, Swift, Python, TypeScript, Vanilla JS</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stack-item">
              <span class="stack-label">AI</span>
              <span class="stack-value">Claude API, Ollama, Whisper, PyAnnote</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stack-item">
              <span class="stack-label">Infrastructure</span>
              <span class="stack-value">Caddy, Gitea, GitHub Actions, Tailscale</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stack-item">
              <span class="stack-label">Methodology</span>
              <span class="stack-value">AI-native multi-agent development</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section animate-fade-in animate-delay-4">
          <h2>Links</h2>
          <div class="link-grid">
            <a href="https://github.com/WastelandWares" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ext-link">
              <span class="ext-label">GitHub</span>
              <span class="ext-desc">Open source code &rarr;</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://papers.wastelandwares.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ext-link">
              <span class="ext-label">Whitepapers</span>
              <span class="ext-desc">Research & writing &rarr;</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://dungeoncrawler.wastelandwares.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ext-link">
              <span class="ext-label">Dungeon Crawler</span>
              <span class="ext-desc">Play the game &rarr;</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: var(--space-16) 0;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 55ch;
  }

  .about-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-section p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Stack list */
  .stack-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .stack-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }

  .stack-label {
    color: var(--cyan);
    font-weight: 600;
    min-width: 120px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .stack-value {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Links grid */
  .link-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .ext-link {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background var(--transition-fast), border-color var(--transition-fast), transform var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .ext-link:hover {
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
    border-color: var(--border-accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .ext-label {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .ext-desc {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .ext-link:hover .ext-desc {
    color: var(--cyan);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .stack-item { flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-1); }
    .stack-label { min-width: auto; }
    .link-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
